		<div id="comment_body_64768726"><p>I started writing a diatribe on why various suggested changes may won't work, but there are so many variables that I decided it's not realistic to forecast the results without actual road-testing.</p><p>Corporations, colleges, and students all want to "game the system" in their favor, and taking away one lever from them will just cause them to juice the remaining levers in ways that are hard to predict when combined with each entity, as it's a cat-and-mouse-and-dog game: a 3-body-problem.</p></div>
	</div>

