	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64768800"><p>Was the course work hard enough that some (hopefully, small) percentage of the class failed?  Was the course work demanding enough that only a small percentage of the class could achieve excellence?  If the graded curve seems unreasonable or unfair, I'll settle for the Bell curve - but I need some way to gauge a college graduate's ability to succeed in the competitive real world.  The real world's not fair, teaching students to expect otherwise would be a mistake.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64768800">

</div>
